distorOrdPrc.ordInstr: Call (202-366-DATA), fax (202-366-3640), or E-mail (answers@bts.gov) RITA/BTS to request the National Transportation Atlas Databases (NTAD) 2012 DVD. The NTAD DVD can be ordered from the online bookstore at www.bts.gov. Individual datasets from the NTAD can also be downloaded from the Office of Geospatial Information Systems website at http://www.bts.gov/programs/geographic_information_services/

distorFormat.fileDecmTech: No compression applied. However, if using digital transfer online option, note access instructions.

dataIdInfo.idAbs: The NBI is a collection of information (database) describing the more than 600,000 of the Nation's bridges located on public roads, including Interstate Highways, U.S. highways, State and county roads, as well as publicly-accessible bridges on Federal lands. It presents a State by State summary analysis of the number, location, and general condition of highway bridges within each State.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: To document the nation's bridge inventory.

rpCntInfo.cntInstr: Federal Highway Administration 1200 New Jersey Ave., SE Washington, DC 20590

Consts.useLimit: The NBI database, or any portion thereof, can be freely distributed as long as this metadata entry is included with each distribution. The original metadata entry cannot be modified or deleted from any data transfer.

report.measDesc: RITA/BTS quality checks were to cross reference the NBI dataset with an up-to-date TeleAtlas dataset, to determine that the spatial data and attribute data were accurate. For those bridges that were not matched to the TeleAtlas data, an attempt was made to use the State supplied longitude-latitude data contained in the NBI. If the resulting point fell within the State, then that location was used. If the point fell outside of the State, it is coded to longitude-latitude 0-0. See the STATUS attribute for more information.
